      ],
      "title": "Returns"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The name sinc is short for \"sine cardinal\" or \"sinus cardinalis\"."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The sinc function is used in various signal processing applications,\nincluding in anti-aliasing, in the construction of a Lanczos resampling\nfilter, and in interpolation."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "For bandlimited interpolation of discrete-time signals, the ideal\ninterpolation kernel is proportional to the sinc function."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nWeisstein, Eric W. \"Sinc Function.\" From MathWorld--A Wolfram Web\nResource. https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SincFunction.html",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nWikipedia, \"Sinc function\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sinc_function",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
